[size=14pt][b][color=#00ff00]🤖 DISTRIBUTED AI INFERENCE (NEW!)[/color][/b][/size]

Q-NarwhalKnight v0.1.9-beta introduces [b]horizontal AI scaling[/b] - the first blockchain to distribute AI inference across network nodes using [b]libp2p + Gossipsub[/b] coordination.

[b]Architecture:[/b]
[code]
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│        Q-NarwhalKnight P2P Network                   │
│     libp2p + Gossipsub + Kademlia DHT                │
│                                                       │
│  Gossipsub Topics (5):                               │
│  - qnk/ai/inference-request/v1                       │
│  - qnk/ai/layer-output/v1                            │
│  - qnk/ai/node-capability/v1                         │
│  - qnk/ai/coordinator/v1                             │
│  - qnk/ai/heartbeat/v1                               │
└───────────┬──────────────────────┬───────────────────┘
            │                      │
    ┌───────▼────────┐     ┌──────▼───────┐
    │  Node A        │◄───►│   Node B     │
    │  Coordinator   │     │  Participant │
    │  CUDA 24GB     │     │  Metal 32GB  │
    │  Layers 0-15   │     │ Layers 16-26 │
    └────────────────┘     └──────────────┘
[/code]

[b]Key Features:[/b]
• [b]Automatic Hardware Detection[/b] - CUDA/Metal/CPU capability scoring
• [b]Layer-Parallel Processing[/b] - 32 layers distributed across nodes (Mistral-7B)
• [b]Graceful Fallback[/b] - Single-node inference when distributed nodes unavailable
• [b]Real-time Statistics[/b] - Token throughput, latency, nodes used tracking
• [b]Gossipsub Coordination[/b] - P2P discovery and layer assignment

[b]Performance Targets:[/b]
• [b]Single Node:[/b] 0.51 tok/s (CPU baseline)
• [b]3-Node Distributed:[/b] 2.86 tok/s target (5.6× speedup)
• [b]Latency:[/b] 350-578ms per token (distributed)

[b]How It Works:[/b]
1. Client creates chat with [b]distributed_enabled: true[/b]
2. Coordinator queries available nodes via gossipsub
3. Nodes announce hardware capabilities (CUDA/Metal/CPU)
4. Inference request published to network
5. (Phase 2) Layers assigned based on capability scores
6. (Phase 2) Sequential layer execution with tensor forwarding
7. Tokens streamed back to client in real-time

[b]Usage:[/b]
[code]
# AI enabled by default (v0.1.9-beta)
./q-api-server --port 8080

# Disable AI to save ~4GB RAM:
export Q_DISABLE_AI=1
./q-api-server --port 8080

# Create distributed chat via API:
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/chat/new \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"user_id": "test", "title": "Distributed Test", "distributed_enabled": true}'
[/code]

[hr]

[size=14pt][b][color=#00ff00]💬 CHAT UI FIXES (CRITICAL)[/color][/b][/size]

[b]Problem:[/b] Users reported AI chat stopping mid-sentence after ~150 tokens, with messages vanishing when browsing away.

[b]Root Causes Found:[/b]
❌ max_tokens defaulted to only 150 tokens (mid-sentence cutoffs)
❌ Partial responses not saved on client disconnect
❌ EventSource error handlers clearing message state

[b]Solutions Implemented:[/b]
✅ Increased max_tokens from 150 → 2048 (full responses up to ~2000 words)
✅ Save partial responses on client disconnect (no data loss)
✅ Improved EventSource error handling (messages persist)
✅ Double requestAnimationFrame for correct rendering timing

[b]Before vs After:[/b]
[table]
[tr][td][b]Metric[/b][/td][td][b]BEFORE[/b][/td][td][b]AFTER[/b][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Max Response[/td][td]~150 tokens (~150 words)[/td][td]2048 tokens (~2000 words)[/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Message Persistence[/td][td]❌ Vanishes on disconnect[/td][td]✅ Saves partial responses[/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Browse Away[/td][td]❌ Messages lost[/td][td]✅ Messages persist[/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Error Recovery[/td][td]❌ State cleared[/td][td]✅ Auto-loads from storage[/td][/tr]
[/table]

[b]Technical Details:[/b]
• [b]Model:[/b] Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3 (Q4_K_M quantization)
• [b]Context Window:[/b] 8192 tokens
• [b]Response Limit:[/b] 2048 tokens (leaving room for prompt)
• [b]Storage:[/b] RocksDB ai_chats column family
• [b]Streaming:[/b] Server-Sent Events (SSE) with cumulative text tracking

[hr]

[size=14pt][b][color=#00ff00]🌐 ENHANCED P2P NETWORKING[/color][/b][/size]

[b]Critical Peer Discovery Fix:[/b]
Fixed zero peer count issue that prevented nodes from discovering each other on the network.

[b]Network Stack:[/b]
• [b]libp2p[/b] - Modular P2P networking framework
• [b]Gossipsub[/b] - Efficient pub/sub messaging (5 AI topics)
• [b]Kademlia DHT[/b] - Distributed hash table for peer discovery
• [b]QUIC Transport[/b] - High-performance UDP-based protocol
• [b]mDNS[/b] - Local network peer discovery

[b]Topics:[/b]
[code]
/qnk/blocks/v1          - Block propagation
/qnk/transactions/v1    - Transaction gossip
/qnk/ack/v1             - Acknowledgements
/qnk/ai/*               - Distributed AI coordination (5 topics)
[/code]

