[size=14pt][b][color=#00ff00]🧬 QUANTUM CONSENSUS TECHNOLOGY[/color][/b][/size]

Q-NarwhalKnight combines [b]DAG-Knight zero-message consensus[/b] with [b]Narwhal's reliable mempool[/b] for a revolutionary quantum-enhanced blockchain.

[b]Core Components:[/b]

[b]1. DAG-Knight Consensus[/b]
• Zero-message BFT consensus (no leader election overhead)
• Quantum-enhanced anchor election via VDF
• Byzantine fault tolerance (f < n/3)
• Deterministic finality in 2-3 rounds

[b]2. Narwhal Mempool[/b]
• Reliable broadcast using Bracha's protocol
• High-throughput transaction ordering
• Parallel block production
• Decoupled execution from consensus

[b]3. Post-Quantum Cryptography[/b]
• [b]Phase 0:[/b] Ed25519 signatures + QUIC transport
• [b]Phase 1:[/b] Dilithium5 + Kyber1024 (crypto-agile framework)
• [b]Phase 2:[/b] QKD integration (planned)
• [b]Phase 3+:[/b] Full quantum resistance

[b]4. Distributed AI Inference[/b]
• Horizontal scaling across network nodes
• Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3 integration
• Layer-parallel processing (32 layers)
• Gossipsub coordination protocol

[b]Performance Characteristics:[/b]
• [b]Throughput:[/b] 100,000+ TPS
• [b]Finality:[/b] <50ms (single-node), <2.9s (distributed with Tor)
• [b]Consensus Latency:[/b] 2-3 rounds
• [b]Byzantine Tolerance:[/b] f < n/3
• [b]AI Inference:[/b] 0.51 tok/s (single), 2.86 tok/s target (distributed)

